text: Buckingham House in Pall Mall, London was a residence of the Dukes of Buckingham and Chandos, designed by the Neoclassical architect Sir John Soane in 1790. Soane employed the Palladian style for the three-storey-high frontage. The construction work finished in 1795. The house was demolished in 1908 and, today, Royal Automobile Club occupies the site. ==Bibliography== * ==References== Category:Historic buildings and structures in England Category:John Soane buildings Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1795 Category:History of the City of Westminster Category:Houses completed in the 18th century Category:Former houses in the City of Westminster Category:Buildings and structures demolished in 1908 Category:Palladian architecture in England
title: Buckingham House, Pall Mall
